
[1]ingratitude

   INGRAT'ITUDE, n.

   1. Want of gratitude or sentiments of kindness for favors received;
   insensibility to favors,and want of a disposition to repay them;
   unthankfulness.

   Ingratitude is abhorred by God and man.

   No man will own himself guilty of ingratitude.

   2. Retribution of evil for good.

   Nor was it with ingratitude returned.
